---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Mapping the Known Universe: A 3D Journey | Geet Purohit';
const description =
  'A fullscreen, navigable 3D map of the scanned universe built from real open survey data: 2 million stars from the AT-HYG (Gaia/Tycho) catalogue and 620,000+ galaxies from the 2MASS and SDSS surveys. Fly from the solar system out to the cosmic web on one continuous scale, rendered live in your browser.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="uni-root">
    <canvas id="uni"></canvas>
    <div class="u-labels" id="labels"></div>

    <!-- top-left -->
    <div class="ui-tl">
      <a class="back" href="/#projects">← geetpurohit.com</a>
      <div class="title-row">
        <span class="pulse"></span>
        <span class="ui-title">Mapping the Known Universe</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- top-right: scale readout -->
    <div class="ui-tr" id="scaleHud">
      <div class="scale-layer" id="layerName">Local stellar neighborhood</div>
      <div class="scale-span" id="spanText">30 light years across</div>
      <div class="scale-dot" id="dotText">Each point is a star</div>
      <div class="scale-source" id="sourceText">AT-HYG (Gaia) catalogue · 1,999,778 real stars</div>
    </div>

    <!-- loading -->
    <div class="uni-loading" id="loading">
      <div class="spinner"></div>
      <span id="loadPct">Loading the universe…</span>
    </div>

    <!-- bottom controls -->
    <div class="ui-bottom">
      <div class="jump-group">
        <button class="hud-btn" data-log="-3.6">Solar system</button>
        <button class="hud-btn active" data-log="1.2">Neighborhood</button>
        <button class="hud-btn" data-log="4.6">Milky Way</button>
        <button class="hud-btn" data-log="7.6">Supercluster</button>
        <button class="hud-btn" data-log="8.9">Cosmic web</button>
      </div>
      <input id="zoom" class="zoom-slider" type="range" min="0" max="1" step="0.0005" value="0.420" aria-label="Zoom scale" />
      <button class="hud-btn ai-btn" id="aiBtn" aria-label="Toggle AI reconstruction">✦ AI fill: off</button>
      <button class="hud-btn info-btn" id="infoBtn" aria-label="About this map">i</button>
    </div>
    <div class="ui-hint">Scroll to travel through scale · drag to orbit</div>

    <!-- info overlay -->
    <div class="info-panel" id="infoPanel" hidden>
      <button class="info-close" id="infoClose" aria-label="Close">×</button>
      <h2>How this map is built</h2>
      <p>Every star and galaxy sits at its <strong>real measured position</strong>, in one continuous
        space. There are no separate "levels", you are flying through a single 3D model on a
        logarithmic scale, so structures nest the way they truly do: the neighborhood inside the
        galaxy, the galaxy inside the cosmic web.</p>
      <p><strong>The stars</strong> come from the AT-HYG catalogue (Hipparcos, Tycho and Gaia),
        nearly 2 million of them with measured distances, colored by their real temperature: hot
        blue-white giants, our yellow Sun, cool red Antares. They form a bubble a few thousand light
        years across, the limit of where stellar distances can actually be measured, including the
        real stars above and below the galactic plane.</p>
      <p><strong>The galaxies</strong> come from two redshift surveys, 620,033 of them placed by
        their measured redshift through Hubble's law: the all-sky 2MASS survey for the local sphere,
        and the deep SDSS survey for the great wedge that reaches out past 500 million light years.
        The cosmic web, its filaments, walls and voids, is not drawn; it falls out of the data.</p>
      <p>Between the galaxy and the deep web sits the <strong>Local Group and Local Supercluster</strong>:
        real nearby galaxies at their measured distances, Andromeda, the Magellanic Clouds, Centaurus A,
        the Whirlpool, and the Virgo Cluster that anchors our supercluster. The bright galaxies here are
        real, from the 2MASS Redshift Survey, weighted by their measured luminosity so cluster cores glow.</p>
      <p><strong>The glowing web at the supercluster scale is a reconstruction.</strong> A real survey is
        a sparse scatter of galaxies, not the continuous filaments you see in simulation images, so the
        soft web behind the real galaxies is modeled: the bright nodes sit at the true positions of Virgo,
        Coma, the Great Attractor and the other real clusters, and the filaments and voids between them
        come from a Voronoi-foam model of the cosmic web, boosted to follow the real 2MASS density. The
        structure is a plausible reconstruction, not an observation; the real galaxies ride on top of it.</p>
      <p><strong>Some things are honest models, not surveys.</strong> The planets sit at their real
        orbital distances, and the asteroid belt, Kuiper belt, heliopause and Oort cloud are drawn at
        their real distances too, but as representative clouds, we have no catalogue of individual
        Oort cloud objects. The two <strong>Voyager probes</strong> sit at their real 2026 positions,
        the only human-made objects out there, already past the heliopause and climbing out of the
        ecliptic plane. And the far Milky Way is a schematic spiral, because we sit inside our
        galaxy and cannot measure most of its stars; the real stars fill the bubble around the Sun,
        then blend into the model beyond.</p>
      <p><strong>The halo is real again.</strong> Surrounding the disc, the roughly 150 globular
        clusters (Harris catalogue) and the dwarf satellite galaxies (Sagittarius, Fornax, Sculptor,
        Draco, Leo I and dozens more, from the McConnachie catalogue) sit at their real measured
        distances, filling the space from the disc edge out to the Local Group that would otherwise
        look empty.</p>
      <p><strong style="color:#ff7ac6">The "AI fill" toggle</strong> is different from everything else:
        it is <strong>not real data</strong>. A 3D diffusion model I trained on simulated cosmic-web
        fields dreams up plausible galaxies to fill the sky the surveys never saw, behind the Milky Way
        and outside the SDSS wedge, so you can imagine what the whole cosmic web might look like. It is
        statistically web-like but invented; the crimson points are inferred, never observed.</p>
      <p class="info-src">Data: AT-HYG / HYG (astronexus, public domain) · 2MRS (Huchra et al. 2012) ·
        SDSS · globular clusters (Harris 1996, 2010 ed.) · Local Group dwarfs (McConnachie 2012).
        Rendered with Three.js. <a href="https://github.com/geetpurohit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Code on GitHub</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <p id="uni-fallback" class="uni-fallback" hidden>
      Your browser could not start WebGL, so the 3D map cannot render.
      <a href="/">Return home</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <script>
    import * as THREE from 'three';

    const canvas = document.getElementById('uni');
    const root = document.querySelector('.uni-root');
    const labelBox = document.getElementById('labels');
    const loading = document.getElementById('loading');
    const loadPct = document.getElementById('loadPct');
    const fallback = document.getElementById('uni-fallback');
    const layerNameEl = document.getElementById('layerName');
    const spanTextEl = document.getElementById('spanText');
    const dotTextEl = document.getElementById('dotText');
    const sourceTextEl = document.getElementById('sourceText');
    const zoom = document.getElementById('zoom');

    let GAL_SOURCE = '2MASS + SDSS surveys · 620,033 real galaxies';
    let SUPERCLUSTER_SOURCE = 'Laniakea · 2MASS Redshift Survey';
    let WEBFILL_COUNT = 0, webfillOn = false, SUPERCLUSTER_COUNT = 0, SUPWEB_COUNT = 0;

    const AU = 4.8481e-6;          // parsecs per AU
    const PC_TO_LY = 3.2616;
    const LOG_MIN = -4.6, LOG_MAX = 9.2;
    const logToSlider = (l) => (l - LOG_MIN) / (LOG_MAX - LOG_MIN);
    const sliderToLog = (v) => LOG_MIN + v * (LOG_MAX - LOG_MIN);

    let renderer;
    try { renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({ canvas, antialias: true, alpha: false }); }
    catch (e) { renderer = null; }
    if (!renderer) { fallback.hidden = false; loading.style.display = 'none'; }
    else run(renderer);

    function run(renderer) {
      renderer.setClearColor(0x01010a, 1);
      const scene = new THREE.Scene();
      const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(60, 1, 0.001, 1e12);

      // ---------- shared point shader (size scales with camera distance) ----------
      const vert = `
        attribute vec3 aColor;
        attribute float aSize;
        uniform float uSize;
        uniform float uPixelRatio;
        uniform float uFadeR;
        varying vec3 vColor;
        varying float vFade;
        varying float vDim;
        void main() {
          vColor = aColor;
          // soft outer taper (from origin) so the star bubble dissolves instead of ending in a circle
          vFade = uFadeR > 0.5 ? (1.0 - smoothstep(uFadeR * 0.5, uFadeR, length(position))) : 1.0;
          vec4 mv = modelViewMatrix * vec4(position, 1.0);
          float sz = aSize * uSize * uPixelRatio / max(-mv.z, 1e-9);
          // flux-conserving points: an unresolved source cannot shrink below ~1 pixel, so
          // below that hold the footprint and dim by the lost area (brightness ~ 1/dist^2).
          // this removes sub-pixel twinkle and gives real distance-based brightness.
          float minPx = 1.5 * uPixelRatio;
          vDim = 1.0;
          if (sz < minPx) { float t = sz / minPx; vDim = t * t; sz = minPx; }
          gl_PointSize = clamp(sz, 0.0, 52.0);
          gl_Position = projectionMatrix * mv;
        }`;
      const frag = `
        precision mediump float;
        uniform float uOpacity;
        uniform float uSat;
        varying vec3 vColor;
        varying float vFade;
        varying float vDim;
        void main() {
          float d = length(gl_PointCoord - 0.5);
          float a = smoothstep(0.5, 0.05, d) * vFade * vDim;
          if (a <= 0.001) discard;
          // keep the physical hue: saturate around luminance, brighten the core without going white
          vec3 c = vColor;
          float l = dot(c, vec3(0.2126, 0.7152, 0.0722));
          c = clamp(mix(vec3(l), c, uSat), 0.0, 1.0);
          float core = smoothstep(0.30, 0.0, d) * 0.6;
          c += core * mix(vec3(1.0), c, 0.6);
          gl_FragColor = vec4(c, a * uOpacity);
        }`;
      function makeMat() {
        return new THREE.ShaderMaterial({
          uniforms: { uOpacity: { value: 1 }, uSize: { value: 1 }, uPixelRatio: { value: renderer.getPixelRatio() }, uFadeR: { value: 0 }, uSat: { value: 1.35 } },
          vertexShader: vert, fragmentShader: frag,
          transparent: true, depthWrite: false, depthTest: false, blending: THREE.AdditiveBlending,
        });
      }

      const groups = {};
      // big datasets: Float32 positions + Uint8 (rgb,size) interleaved
      function pointsPacked(posBuf, colBuf) {
        const geo = new THREE.BufferGeometry();
        geo.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(posBuf), 3));
        const inter = new THREE.InterleavedBuffer(new Uint8Array(colBuf), 4);
        geo.setAttribute('aColor', new THREE.InterleavedBufferAttribute(inter, 3, 0, true));
        geo.setAttribute('aSize', new THREE.InterleavedBufferAttribute(inter, 1, 3, true));
        const pts = new THREE.Points(geo, makeMat());
        pts.frustumCulled = false;
        return pts;
      }
      // small datasets: plain Float32 attributes
      function pointsFloat(pos, col, size) {
        const geo = new THREE.BufferGeometry();
        geo.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(pos), 3));
        geo.setAttribute('aColor', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(col), 3));
        geo.setAttribute('aSize', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(size), 1));
        const pts = new THREE.Points(geo, makeMat());
        pts.frustumCulled = false;
        return pts;
      }

      // ---------- labels ----------
      const labelDefs = [];
      const addLabel = (name, x, y, z, band, cls) => {
        const el = document.createElement('div');
        el.className = 'u-label ' + (cls || '');
        el.textContent = name;
        labelBox.appendChild(el);
        labelDefs.push({ el, pos: new THREE.Vector3(x, y, z), band });
      };

      // ---------- solar system (real orbital distances, Sun at origin) ----------
      function buildSolarSystem() {
        const planets = [
          // real observed colors
          ['Mercury', 0.39, 0.62, 0.59, 0.55], ['Venus', 0.72, 0.96, 0.90, 0.72],
          ['Earth', 1.00, 0.30, 0.55, 0.95], ['Mars', 1.52, 0.86, 0.42, 0.26],
          ['Jupiter', 5.20, 0.86, 0.74, 0.58], ['Saturn', 9.58, 0.92, 0.82, 0.58],
          ['Uranus', 19.2, 0.66, 0.90, 0.92], ['Neptune', 30.05, 0.26, 0.45, 0.86],
        ];
        const pos = [], col = [], size = [];
        const push = (x, y, z, r, g, b, s) => { pos.push(x, y, z); col.push(r, g, b); size.push(s); };
        const grp = new THREE.Group();
        // Sun
        push(0, 0, 0, 1.0, 0.85, 0.45, 9);
        addLabel('The Sun', 0, 0, 0, 'solar', 'sun');
        // planets + orbit rings
        for (const [name, a, r, g, b] of planets) {
          const ang = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2, R = a * AU;
          const x = R * Math.cos(ang), z = R * Math.sin(ang);
          push(x, 0, z, r, g, b, 4.2);
          addLabel(name, x, 0, z, 'solar');
          const seg = 200, arr = new Float32Array((seg + 1) * 3);
          for (let i = 0; i <= seg; i++) {
            const t = (i / seg) * Math.PI * 2;
            arr[i * 3] = R * Math.cos(t); arr[i * 3 + 1] = 0; arr[i * 3 + 2] = R * Math.sin(t);
          }
          const lg = new THREE.BufferGeometry();
          lg.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(arr, 3));
          const lm = new THREE.LineBasicMaterial({ color: 0x8a7fff, transparent: true, opacity: 0.25, depthTest: false, depthWrite: false });
          grp.add(new THREE.LineLoop(lg, lm));
        }
        // Asteroid belt (between Mars and Jupiter, ~2.1-3.3 AU)
        for (let i = 0; i < 2600; i++) {
          const a = (2.1 + Math.random() * 1.2) * AU, ang = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
          push(a * Math.cos(ang), gauss() * a * 0.05, a * Math.sin(ang), 0.68, 0.62, 0.54, 1.3 + Math.random() * 0.7);
        }
        addLabel('Asteroid belt', 2.7 * AU, 0, 0, 'solar', 'faint');
        // Kuiper belt (~30-50 AU)
        for (let i = 0; i < 4000; i++) {
          const a = (30 + Math.random() * 20) * AU, ang = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
          push(a * Math.cos(ang), gauss() * a * 0.09, a * Math.sin(ang), 0.6, 0.75, 0.9, 1.3 + Math.random() * 0.8);
        }
        addLabel('Kuiper belt', 42 * AU, 0, 0, 'solar', 'faint');
        // Comets / scattered disc (eccentric orbits)
        for (let i = 0; i < 70; i++) {
          const q = (0.6 + Math.random() * 4) * AU, Q = (45 + Math.random() * 450) * AU;
          const aa = (q + Q) / 2, e = (Q - q) / (Q + q), nu = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
          const rr = aa * (1 - e * e) / (1 + e * Math.cos(nu)), inc = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 1.3;
          push(rr * Math.cos(nu), rr * Math.sin(nu) * Math.sin(inc), rr * Math.sin(nu) * Math.cos(inc), 0.7, 0.92, 1.0, 1.6 + Math.random());
        }
        // Heliosphere / heliopause shell (~120 AU)
        for (let i = 0; i < 2400; i++) {
          const rr = (112 + Math.random() * 16) * AU, u = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2, v = Math.acos(2 * Math.random() - 1);
          push(rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.cos(u), rr * Math.cos(v), rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.sin(u), 0.3, 0.5, 0.85, 0.85 + Math.random() * 0.5);
        }
        addLabel('Heliopause', 120 * AU, 0, 0, 'solar', 'faint');
        // Voyager 1 & 2 — real ~2026 positions (AU, ecliptic lon/lat deg); the farthest human-made objects
        for (const [name, dAU, lon, lat] of [['Voyager 1', 166, 255, 35], ['Voyager 2', 139, 290, -48]]) {
          const lo = lon * Math.PI / 180, la = lat * Math.PI / 180, D = dAU * AU;
          const x = D * Math.cos(la) * Math.cos(lo), y = D * Math.sin(la), z = D * Math.cos(la) * Math.sin(lo);
          push(x, y, z, 1.0, 0.86, 0.6, 4.6);
          addLabel(name, x, y, z, 'solar');
          const tg = new THREE.BufferGeometry();
          tg.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array([0, 0, 0, x, y, z]), 3));
          grp.add(new THREE.Line(tg, new THREE.LineBasicMaterial({ color: 0x9fd8ff, transparent: true, opacity: 0.3, depthTest: false, depthWrite: false })));
        }
        // Oort cloud (~2,000 - 100,000 AU spherical shell, log-distributed)
        for (let i = 0; i < 12000; i++) {
          const rr = Math.pow(10, 3.3 + Math.random() * 1.7) * AU, u = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2, v = Math.acos(2 * Math.random() - 1);
          push(rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.cos(u), rr * Math.cos(v), rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.sin(u), 0.75, 0.78, 0.86, 0.6 + Math.random() * 0.5);
        }
        addLabel('Oort cloud', 45000 * AU, 0, 0, 'solar', 'faint');

        const pts = pointsFloat(pos, col, size);
        grp.add(pts);
        grp.userData.pts = pts;
        grp.userData.lines = grp.children.filter((c) => c.isLine); // orbit rings + Voyager trajectories
        return grp;
      }

      // ---------- Local Group + nearby galaxies (real distances) ----------
      function buildLocalGroup() {
        // [name, distance Mpc, RA deg, Dec deg, showLabel]
        const G = [
          ['Andromeda (M31)', 0.78, 10.68, 41.27, 1], ['Triangulum (M33)', 0.85, 23.46, 30.66, 1],
          ['Large Magellanic Cloud', 0.050, 80.0, -69.76, 1], ['Small Magellanic Cloud', 0.062, 13.19, -72.83, 0],
          ['NGC 6822', 0.50, 296.24, -14.80, 0], ['IC 10', 0.66, 5.10, 59.29, 0], ['NGC 300', 2.0, 13.72, -37.68, 0],
          ['Sculptor Galaxy', 3.5, 11.89, -25.29, 1], ['Centaurus A', 3.8, 201.36, -43.02, 1],
          ['M81', 3.6, 148.89, 69.07, 1], ['M82 (Cigar)', 3.5, 148.97, 69.68, 0], ['M83', 4.9, 204.25, -29.87, 0],
          ['M94', 4.7, 192.72, 41.12, 0], ['M101 (Pinwheel)', 6.4, 210.80, 54.35, 1], ['M51 (Whirlpool)', 8.6, 202.47, 47.20, 1],
          ['M104 (Sombrero)', 9.6, 190.00, -11.62, 1], ['M87 (Virgo Cluster)', 16.4, 187.71, 12.39, 1],
          ['M49', 16.5, 187.44, 8.00, 0], ['M86', 16.0, 186.55, 12.95, 0], ['M60', 16.5, 190.92, 11.55, 0],
          ['Antennae', 20.0, 180.47, -18.87, 0],
        ];
        const MPC = 1e6, pos = [], col = [], size = [];
        for (const [name, d, ra, dec, lab] of G) {
          const rr = ra * Math.PI / 180, dd = dec * Math.PI / 180, D = d * MPC;
          const x = D * Math.cos(dd) * Math.cos(rr), y = D * Math.cos(dd) * Math.sin(rr), z = D * Math.sin(dd);
          pos.push(x, y, z); col.push(0.82, 0.86, 1.0); size.push(3.8);
          if (lab) addLabel(name, x, y, z, 'localgroup', 'faint');
        }
        return pointsFloat(pos, col, size);
      }

      // ---------- named clusters & voids of the Local Supercluster / Laniakea ----------
      function addSuperclusterLabels() {
        const MPC = 1e6;
        // [name, RA deg, Dec deg, distance Mpc, class]
        const C = [
          ['Virgo Cluster', 187.7, 12.4, 16.5, ''], ['Fornax Cluster', 54.6, -35.4, 19, ''],
          ['Eridanus Cluster', 55.0, -21.0, 23, 'faint'], ['Ursa Major Cloud', 180.5, 55.0, 18, 'faint'],
          ['Centaurus Cluster', 192.2, -41.3, 45, ''], ['Hydra Cluster', 159.2, -27.5, 50, 'faint'],
          ['Antlia Cluster', 157.5, -35.3, 40, 'faint'],
          ['Great Attractor (Norma)', 243.6, -60.8, 68, ''], ['Perseus Cluster', 49.95, 41.5, 74, ''],
          ['Coma Cluster', 194.9, 27.9, 100, ''], ['Leo Cluster', 176.1, 19.8, 92, 'faint'],
          ['Hercules Cluster', 241.3, 17.7, 160, 'faint'], ['Shapley Supercluster', 202.0, -31.0, 200, ''],
          ['Local Void', 288.0, 15.0, 30, 'faint'],
        ];
        for (const [name, ra, dec, d, cls] of C) {
          const rr = ra * Math.PI / 180, dd = dec * Math.PI / 180, D = d * MPC;
          addLabel(name, D * Math.cos(dd) * Math.cos(rr), D * Math.cos(dd) * Math.sin(rr), D * Math.sin(dd), 'supercluster', cls);
        }
      }

      // ---------- Milky Way model (real galactocentric scale, Sun at origin) ----------
      function gauss() { return (Math.random() + Math.random() + Math.random() - 1.5) / 1.5; }
      function buildMilkyWay() {
        const R = 15000;      // disk radius, pc
        const CX = -8000;     // galactic center (Sun at origin, 8000 pc out)
        const pos = [], col = [], size = [];
        const push = (x, y, z, r, g, b, s) => { pos.push(x, y, z); col.push(r, g, b); size.push(s); };
        // keep-probability near the Sun -> 0, so the real star bubble fills the hole (no "pimple")
        const keepNearSun = (x, y, z) => Math.min(1, Math.max(0, (Math.sqrt(x * x + y * y + z * z) - 500) / 2200));

        // 1) spiral disk: 2 major arms + diffuse inter-arm field, flocculent + dust
        const Narm = 95000;
        for (let i = 0; i < Narm; i++) {
          const rr = Math.pow(Math.random(), 0.7) * R;
          const diffuse = Math.random() < 0.45;
          let th;
          if (diffuse) th = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
          else {
            const arm = Math.floor(Math.random() * 2);
            th = arm * Math.PI + Math.log(rr / 500 + 1) * 2.3 + (0.16 + 0.16 * (rr / R)) * gauss() * Math.PI;
          }
          if (Math.random() < Math.max(0, (rr - R * 0.82) / (R * 0.18))) continue; // soft outer edge
          const x = CX + rr * Math.cos(th) + R * 0.01 * gauss();
          const z = rr * Math.sin(th) + R * 0.01 * gauss();
          const y = gauss() * (150 + 110 * (rr / R)); // thin-disk scale height grows outward
          if (Math.random() > keepNearSun(x, y, z)) continue;
          const tr = rr / R, roll = Math.random();
          let r, g, b, s;
          if (!diffuse && roll < 0.06) { r = 1.0; g = 0.55; b = 0.72; s = 0.6 + Math.random() * 0.7; }      // HII pink
          else if (!diffuse && roll < 0.12) { r = 0.6; g = 0.78; b = 1.0; s = 0.6 + Math.random() * 0.7; }  // blue OB
          else {
            const w = diffuse ? 0 : 0.14;
            r = 0.7 + w + 0.2 * (1 - tr); g = 0.68 + 0.1 * (1 - tr); b = 0.66 + 0.3 * tr;
            s = 0.32 + Math.random() * 0.4;
          }
          if (Math.random() < 0.16) { r *= 0.45; g *= 0.45; b *= 0.45; } // dust dimming
          push(x, y, z, r, g, b, s);
        }
        // 2) central bar (Milky Way is a barred spiral)
        for (let i = 0; i < 13000; i++) {
          const t = Math.random() - 0.5, ba = 0.42, along = t * 5400;
          push(CX + along * Math.cos(ba) + gauss() * 750, gauss() * 340, along * Math.sin(ba) + gauss() * 750,
               1.0, 0.8, 0.5, 0.45 + Math.random() * 0.55);
        }
        // 3) bulge (spheroid)
        for (let i = 0; i < 16000; i++) {
          const rr = Math.abs(gauss()) * 1900, u = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2, v = Math.acos(2 * Math.random() - 1);
          push(CX + rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.cos(u), rr * Math.cos(v) * 0.65, rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.sin(u),
               1.0, 0.83, 0.52, 0.45 + Math.random() * 0.55);
        }
        // 4) thick disk + spheroidal halo -> real stars ABOVE and BELOW the plane (a model)
        for (let i = 0; i < 26000; i++) {
          let x, y, z;
          if (Math.random() < 0.6) {
            const rr = Math.pow(Math.random(), 0.6) * R, th = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
            x = CX + rr * Math.cos(th); z = rr * Math.sin(th); y = gauss() * 950; // thick disk
          } else {
            const rr = Math.pow(Math.random(), 0.5) * R * 1.15, u = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2, v = Math.acos(2 * Math.random() - 1);
            x = CX + rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.cos(u); y = rr * Math.cos(v) * 0.8; z = rr * Math.sin(v) * Math.sin(u); // halo
          }
          if (Math.random() > keepNearSun(x, y, z)) continue;
          push(x, y, z, 0.85, 0.82, 0.78, 0.28 + Math.random() * 0.32);
        }
        addLabel('Galactic center', CX, 0, 0, 'mw', 'faint');
        return pointsFloat(pos, col, size);
      }

      // ---------- streaming fetch with progress ----------
      async function fetchBuf(url, onProg) {
        const res = await fetch(url);
        const total = +res.headers.get('content-length') || 0;
        if (!res.body || !total) return await res.arrayBuffer();
        const reader = res.body.getReader();
        const chunks = []; let got = 0;
        for (;;) {
          const { done, value } = await reader.read();
          if (done) break;
          chunks.push(value); got += value.length;
          if (onProg) onProg(got / total);
        }
        const out = new Uint8Array(got); let off = 0;
        for (const c of chunks) { out.set(c, off); off += c.length; }
        return out.buffer;
      }

      // ---------- load ----------
      let ready = false;
      (async () => {
        try {
          const meta = await fetch('/universe/meta.json').then((r) => r.json());
          const [sp, sc] = await Promise.all([
            fetchBuf('/universe/stars_pos.bin', (f) => { loadPct.textContent = 'Loading ' + Math.round(f * 100) + '%'; }),
            fetchBuf('/universe/stars_col.bin'),
          ]);
          groups.stars = pointsPacked(sp, sc);
        groups.stars.material.uniforms.uFadeR.value = 6500; // taper the bubble edge (pc from Sun)
        scene.add(groups.stars);

          const [gp, gc] = await Promise.all([
            fetchBuf('/universe/galaxies_pos.bin'), fetchBuf('/universe/galaxies_col.bin'),
          ]);
          groups.gal = pointsPacked(gp, gc); scene.add(groups.gal);

          // dedicated Local Supercluster layer (2MRS, K-luminosity weighted)
          if (meta.supercluster && meta.supercluster.count) {
            try {
              const [scp, scc] = await Promise.all([
                fetchBuf('/universe/supercluster_pos.bin'), fetchBuf('/universe/supercluster_col.bin'),
              ]);
              groups.supercluster = pointsPacked(scp, scc); scene.add(groups.supercluster);
              SUPERCLUSTER_COUNT = meta.supercluster.count;
              SUPERCLUSTER_SOURCE = SUPERCLUSTER_COUNT.toLocaleString() + ' real 2MRS galaxies · web reconstruction';
              addSuperclusterLabels();
            } catch (e) { console.warn('supercluster load failed', e); }
          }

          // reconstructed cosmic web of the Local Supercluster (real nodes + model filaments)
          if (meta.supweb && meta.supweb.count) {
            try {
              const [swp, swc] = await Promise.all([
                fetchBuf('/universe/supweb_pos.bin'), fetchBuf('/universe/supweb_col.bin'),
              ]);
              groups.supweb = pointsPacked(swp, swc); scene.add(groups.supweb);
              groups.supweb.material.uniforms.uFadeR.value = 300e6; // soft rim (pc) so the 210 Mpc ball has no hard edge
              SUPWEB_COUNT = meta.supweb.count;
            } catch (e) { console.warn('supweb load failed', e); }
          }

          // AI-reconstructed cosmic web (synthetic, off by default)
          if (meta.webfill && meta.webfill.count) {
            try {
              const [wp, wc] = await Promise.all([
                fetchBuf('/universe/webfill_pos.bin'), fetchBuf('/universe/webfill_col.bin'),
              ]);
              groups.webfill = pointsPacked(wp, wc); groups.webfill.visible = false; scene.add(groups.webfill);
              WEBFILL_COUNT = meta.webfill.count;
            } catch (e) { console.warn('webfill load failed', e); }
          }

          groups.mw = buildMilkyWay(); scene.add(groups.mw);
          groups.localgroup = buildLocalGroup(); scene.add(groups.localgroup);
          groups.solar = buildSolarSystem(); scene.add(groups.solar);

          // real halo objects: globular clusters + dwarf satellites, filling the disc-to-Local-Group gap
          try {
            const halo = await fetch('/universe/halo.json').then((r) => r.json());
            groups.haloGC = pointsFloat(halo.gc.pos, halo.gc.col, halo.gc.size); scene.add(groups.haloGC);
            groups.haloDW = pointsFloat(halo.dw.pos, halo.dw.col, halo.dw.size); scene.add(groups.haloDW);
            for (const l of halo.labels) addLabel(l.name, l.x, l.y, l.z, 'halo', 'faint');
          } catch (e) { console.warn('halo load failed', e); }

          for (const l of (meta.stars.labels || [])) addLabel(l.name, l.x, l.y, l.z, 'stars');

          loading.style.display = 'none';
          ready = true;
        } catch (err) {
          loadPct.textContent = 'Could not load the map data.';
          console.error(err);
        }
      })();

      // ---------- orbit + zoom ----------
      let az = 0.7, pol = 1.2, tAz = 0.7, tPol = 1.2;
      let dragging = false, lx = 0, ly = 0, interacted = 0;
      let logDist = 1.2, tLog = 1.2;

      root.addEventListener('pointerdown', (e) => {
        if (e.target.closest('.ui-bottom') || e.target.closest('.info-panel') || e.target.closest('.ui-tl') || e.target.closest('.ui-tr')) return;
        dragging = true; lx = e.clientX; ly = e.clientY; interacted = performance.now();
        root.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId); root.classList.add('grabbing');
      });
      root.addEventListener('pointermove', (e) => {
        if (!dragging) return;
        tAz -= (e.clientX - lx) * 0.005; tPol -= (e.clientY - ly) * 0.005;
        tPol = Math.max(0.15, Math.min(Math.PI - 0.15, tPol));
        lx = e.clientX; ly = e.clientY; interacted = performance.now();
      });
      const endDrag = () => { dragging = false; root.classList.remove('grabbing'); };
      root.addEventListener('pointerup', endDrag);
      root.addEventListener('pointercancel', endDrag);

      root.addEventListener('wheel', (e) => {
        if (e.target.closest('.info-panel')) return;
        e.preventDefault();
        tLog = Math.max(LOG_MIN, Math.min(LOG_MAX, tLog + e.deltaY * 0.0011));
        zoom.value = logToSlider(tLog); interacted = performance.now(); syncBtns();
      }, { passive: false });
      zoom.addEventListener('input', () => { tLog = sliderToLog(+zoom.value); syncBtns(); });
      document.querySelectorAll('.hud-btn[data-log]').forEach((b) =>
        b.addEventListener('click', () => { tLog = +b.dataset.log; zoom.value = logToSlider(tLog); interacted = performance.now(); syncBtns(); }));
      function syncBtns() {
        document.querySelectorAll('.hud-btn[data-log]').forEach((b) =>
          b.classList.toggle('active', Math.abs(tLog - (+b.dataset.log)) < 1.3));
      }

      // info panel
      const infoPanel = document.getElementById('infoPanel');
      document.getElementById('infoBtn').addEventListener('click', () => { infoPanel.hidden = !infoPanel.hidden; });
      const aiBtn = document.getElementById('aiBtn');
      aiBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (!groups.webfill) { aiBtn.textContent = '✦ AI fill: loading…'; return; }
        webfillOn = !webfillOn;
        aiBtn.textContent = '✦ AI fill: ' + (webfillOn ? 'on' : 'off');
        aiBtn.classList.toggle('ai-on', webfillOn);
        if (webfillOn && tLog < 6.5) { tLog = 8.3; zoom.value = logToSlider(tLog); }
      });
      document.getElementById('infoClose').addEventListener('click', () => { infoPanel.hidden = true; });

      // ---------- helpers ----------
      const clamp01 = (x) => Math.max(0, Math.min(1, x));
      const sstep = (x, a, b) => clamp01((x - a) / (b - a));
      function fmtScale(camPc) {
        const across = camPc * 1.6; // rough on-screen span
        if (across < 3e-4) return (across / AU).toFixed(1) + ' AU across';
        const ly = across * PC_TO_LY;
        if (ly < 1) return (across / AU).toFixed(0) + ' AU across';
        if (ly < 1e3) return ly.toFixed(ly < 10 ? 1 : 0) + ' light years across';
        if (ly < 1e6) return (ly / 1e3).toFixed(0) + ' thousand light years across';
        if (ly < 1e9) return (ly / 1e6).toFixed(0) + ' million light years across';
        return (ly / 1e9).toFixed(1) + ' billion light years across';
      }
      function layerInfo(L) {
        if (L < -2.0) return ['The solar system', 'Planets, belts, heliosphere & Oort cloud', 'Each point is a planet, asteroid or comet'];
        if (L < 0.8) return ['Nearest stars', 'AT-HYG (Gaia) catalogue · 1,999,778 real stars', 'Each point is a star'];
        if (L < 3.3) return ['Local stellar neighborhood', 'AT-HYG (Gaia) catalogue · 1,999,778 real stars', 'Each point is a star'];
        if (L < 5.0) return ['The Milky Way & halo', 'Model disc + real globular clusters & dwarf satellites', 'Points: galaxy model, real clusters & dwarf galaxies'];
        if (L < 6.6) return ['The Local Group', 'Nearby galaxies · real distances', 'Each point is a galaxy'];
        if (L < 8.4) return ['The Local Supercluster', SUPERCLUSTER_SOURCE, 'Each point is a galaxy'];
        return ['The cosmic web', GAL_SOURCE, 'Each point is an entire galaxy'];
      }

      // ---------- resize ----------
      function resize() {
        const w = window.innerWidth, h = window.innerHeight;
        renderer.setPixelRatio(Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, 2));
        renderer.setSize(w, h, false);
        camera.aspect = w / h; camera.updateProjectionMatrix();
        const pr = renderer.getPixelRatio();
        for (const k in groups) {
          const m = groups[k].userData.pts ? groups[k].userData.pts.material : groups[k].material;
          if (m) m.uniforms.uPixelRatio.value = pr;
        }
      }
      window.addEventListener('resize', resize); resize();

      // ---------- loop ----------
      const tmp = new THREE.Vector3();
      const SIZE_BASE = 2.6;
      function frame() {
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
        logDist += (tLog - logDist) * 0.09;
        const idle = performance.now() - interacted > 4000;
        if (idle && !dragging) tAz += 0.0005;
        az += (tAz - az) * 0.09; pol += (tPol - pol) * 0.09;

        const camPc = Math.pow(10, logDist);
        camera.near = camPc * 1e-3; camera.far = camPc * 1e4; camera.updateProjectionMatrix();
        camera.position.set(
          camPc * Math.sin(pol) * Math.sin(az),
          camPc * Math.cos(pol),
          camPc * Math.sin(pol) * Math.cos(az)
        );
        camera.lookAt(0, 0, 0);
        camera.updateMatrixWorld(); // refresh matrices before projecting labels this frame

        if (ready) {
          const uSize = SIZE_BASE * camPc;
          const op = {
            solar: 1 - sstep(logDist, -0.3, 0.6),
            stars: (1 - sstep(logDist, 3.7, 4.9)) * sstep(logDist, -3.2, -1.6),
            mw: sstep(logDist, 2.4, 3.8) * (1 - sstep(logDist, 5.0, 5.9)),
            halo: sstep(logDist, 3.3, 4.1) * (1 - sstep(logDist, 6.4, 7.2)),
            localgroup: sstep(logDist, 4.2, 5.0) * (1 - sstep(logDist, 7.8, 8.6)),
            supercluster: sstep(logDist, 5.6, 6.6) * (1 - sstep(logDist, 8.2, 8.9)),
            supweb: 1.0 * sstep(logDist, 5.8, 6.8) * (1 - sstep(logDist, 8.0, 8.6)),
            gal: sstep(logDist, 7.9, 8.7),
            webfill: (webfillOn ? 0.7 : 0) * sstep(logDist, 7.9, 8.7),
          };
          const linesOp = 1 - sstep(logDist, -2.6, -1.8); // orbit rings fade when leaving inner system
          const apply = (g, o, linesO) => {
            if (!g) return;
            const pts = g.userData.pts || g;
            pts.visible = o > 0.003;
            pts.material.uniforms.uOpacity.value = o;
            pts.material.uniforms.uSize.value = uSize;
            if (g.userData.lines) { const lo = linesO ?? o; for (const ln of g.userData.lines) { ln.visible = lo > 0.003; ln.material.opacity = 0.25 * lo; } }
          };
          apply(groups.solar, op.solar, linesOp);
          apply(groups.stars, op.stars);
          apply(groups.mw, op.mw);
          apply(groups.haloGC, op.halo);
          apply(groups.haloDW, op.halo);
          apply(groups.localgroup, op.localgroup);
          apply(groups.supweb, op.supweb);
          apply(groups.supercluster, op.supercluster);
          apply(groups.gal, op.gal);
          apply(groups.webfill, op.webfill);

          const [name, src, dot] = layerInfo(logDist);
          layerNameEl.textContent = name; sourceTextEl.textContent = src;
          dotTextEl.textContent = dot;
          spanTextEl.textContent = fmtScale(camPc);

          const w = window.innerWidth, h = window.innerHeight;
          for (const Ld of labelDefs) {
            const o = op[Ld.band] ?? 0;
            if (o < 0.3) { Ld.el.style.opacity = '0'; continue; }
            tmp.copy(Ld.pos).project(camera);
            if (tmp.z > 1 || tmp.z < -1) { Ld.el.style.opacity = '0'; continue; }
            const sx = (tmp.x * 0.5 + 0.5) * w, sy = (-tmp.y * 0.5 + 0.5) * h;
            if (sx < -80 || sx > w + 80 || sy < -40 || sy > h + 40) { Ld.el.style.opacity = '0'; continue; }
            Ld.el.style.transform = `translate(9px,-50%) translate(${sx}px,${sy}px)`;
            Ld.el.style.opacity = String(Math.min(1, o) * 0.9);
          }
        }
        renderer.render(scene, camera);
      }
      frame();
    }
  </script>

  <style is:global>
    html, body { margin: 0; height: 100%; overflow: hidden; background: #01010a; }
  </style>

  <style>
    .uni-root { position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 50; background: #01010a; overflow: hidden; touch-action: none; }
    #uni { position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; cursor: grab; }
    .uni-root.grabbing #uni { cursor: grabbing; }

    .u-labels { position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; overflow: hidden; }
    /* labels are created dynamically, so their styles must be :global to apply */
    :global(.u-label) {
      position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; white-space: nowrap; opacity: 0; transition: opacity .3s;
      font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 11.5px; letter-spacing: 0.02em; color: #eae6ff;
      text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.95), 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.95); will-change: transform;
    }
    :global(.u-label.sun) { color: #ffd27f; }
    :global(.u-label.faint) { color: #7dd3fc; font-size: 10.5px; opacity: 0.85; }

    .ui-tl { position: absolute; top: 20px; left: 22px; z-index: 60; }
    .back { display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); transition: color .25s; }
    .back:hover { color: var(--lilac); }
    .title-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; margin-top: 10px; }
    .ui-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text); }
    .pulse { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #7dd3fc; box-shadow: 0 0 10px #7dd3fc; animation: pulse 1.9s ease-in-out infinite; }
    @keyframes pulse { 0%,100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.3; } }

    .ui-tr { position: absolute; top: 20px; right: 22px; z-index: 60; text-align: right; pointer-events: none; }
    .scale-layer { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(16px, 2.4vw, 22px); color: var(--text); letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .scale-span { font-family: var(--font-mono, ui-monospace, monospace); font-size: 13px; color: #7dd3fc; margin-top: 3px; }
    .scale-dot { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 600; color: #ffd27f; margin-top: 8px; }
    .scale-source { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 3px; }

    .uni-loading { position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 70; display: grid; place-content: center; justify-items: center; gap: 16px; background: #01010a; color: var(--text-dim); font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 14px; }
    .spinner { width: 32px; height: 32px; border-radius: 50%; border: 2px solid rgba(168,130,255,0.2); border-top-color: var(--lilac); animation: spin .9s linear infinite; }
    @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

    .ui-bottom {
      position: absolute; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); bottom: 22px; z-index: 60;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center;
      width: min(880px, calc(100% - 32px)); padding: 10px 12px; border-radius: 14px;
      background: rgba(6,4,14,0.62); border: 1px solid var(--border); backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    }
    .jump-group { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .hud-btn {
      border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 9px; padding: 8px 13px;
      font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); color: var(--text-dim);
      transition: background .15s, border-color .15s, color .15s, transform .08s;
    }
    .hud-btn:hover { background: rgba(168,130,255,0.12); color: var(--text); }
    .hud-btn:active { transform: scale(0.97); }
    .hud-btn.active { background: var(--purple); border-color: transparent; color: #140a24; }
    .info-btn { width: 34px; text-align: center; font-style: italic; font-family: Georgia, serif; }
    .ai-btn { color: #f0a; border-color: rgba(255,60,160,0.35); }
    .ai-btn:hover { background: rgba(255,60,160,0.12); color: #ff7ac6; }
    .ai-btn.ai-on { background: #b02766; border-color: transparent; color: #fff; }
    .zoom-slider {
      flex: 1; min-width: 120px; -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; height: 4px; border-radius: 999px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffd27f, #d8b4fe, #7dd3fc); outline: none; cursor: pointer;
    }
    .zoom-slider::-webkit-slider-thumb { -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; width: 15px; height: 15px; border-radius: 50%; background: #fff; border: 2px solid #1a1230; box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
    .zoom-slider::-moz-range-thumb { width: 15px; height: 15px; border-radius: 50%; background: #fff; border: 2px solid #1a1230; }

    .ui-hint { position: absolute; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); bottom: 4px; z-index: 60; font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); pointer-events: none; }

    .info-panel {
      position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; z-index: 80; width: min(420px, 92vw);
      padding: 60px 34px 34px; overflow-y: auto;
      background: rgba(6,4,16,0.9); border-left: 1px solid var(--border); backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    }
    .info-panel[hidden] { display: none; }
    .info-panel h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--text); }
    .info-panel p { font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .info-panel strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
    .info-src { font-size: 12.5px !important; color: var(--muted) !important; margin-top: 8px; }
    .info-src a { color: var(--lilac); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(168,130,255,0.4); }
    .info-close { position: absolute; top: 18px; right: 18px; width: 34px; height: 34px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); color: var(--text); font-size: 20px; cursor: pointer; }
    .info-close:hover { background: rgba(168,130,255,0.15); }

    .uni-fallback { position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 90; display: grid; place-content: center; text-align: center; gap: 8px; color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 16px; }
    .uni-fallback[hidden] { display: none; }
    .uni-fallback a { color: var(--lilac); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(168,130,255,0.4); }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .ui-tr { top: 64px; }
      .ui-hint { display: none; }
      .jump-group { justify-content: center; }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
